===== Nlg Module =====

Python2 package for analogy purpose.

Version: 1.0
License: This module is under GPLv3 license.

==============================================================================

Dependencies:
1. swig (wrapper for C program)
2. Python libraries:
	- numpy
	- matplotlib
	- tabulate

How to install:
1. fast_distance
	- Download
		http://lepage-lab.ips.waseda.ac.jp/public_cms_data/kakenhi_15K00317/tools/fast_distance_in_c.zip
	- Extract the zip file
	- Open Terminal
	- Install
		>$ cd fast_distance_in_c/
		>$ sudo -H pip install .
2. Nlg
	- Extract the zip file
	- Open Terminal
	- Install
		>$ cd Nlg-1.0/
		>$ sudo -H pip install .

==============================================================================

Use the following command to test the help:
	>$ python2 Words2Clusters.py -h

Use the following commands to test the execution:
	>$ printf "toto\ntata\npopo\npapa\n" | python2 Words2Clusters.py -V

printf "ahah\nohoh\nbaba\nbobo\n" | python2 Words2Clusters.py -V


You should get the following output on your terminal.

	# Reading words and computing feature vectors (features=characters)...
	# Clustering the words according to their feature vectors...
	# Add the indistinguishables...
	# Checking distance constraints...
	# 
	toto : tata :: popo : papa
	toto : popo :: tata : papa

==============================================================================

If you encounter any problem, please do not hesitate to contact us.
